P1 - Lexical Analyzer
CS 4880 Compiler Design

DESCRIPTION
    Reads source code from a file or stdin and emits one line per token in
    the format:
        Group=<type> Instance=<value> Line=<n>
    followed by a final EOFTk line.

BUILD
    If make is available:
        make
        make clean

    Manual (gcc required):
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c P1.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c lexer.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -o P1 P1.o lexer.o

RUN
    ./P1 basename        reads basename.ext
    ./P1 < file.ext      reads from stdin
    ./P1                 reads from stdin (type input, Ctrl+D to end)

TOKEN TYPES
    IDTk      identifier: starts with 'x', followed by letters/digits/underscores, max 8 chars
    IntTk     integer: decimal digits only, max 8 digits
    KW_tk     keyword: go og loop int exit scan output cond then set func program
    OpTk      multi-char operator: ?le ?ge ?lt ?gt ?ne ?eq ** //
    OpDelTk   single-char operator or delimiter: + - : ; = ( ) { } [ ]
    EOFTk     end of input

    Comments (@text@) are consumed silently and do not produce a token.
    Lexical errors print "LEXICAL ERROR: <detail> line <n>" to stderr and exit.

EXAMPLE
    Input file P1_test1.ext:
        2

    Output:
        Group=IntTk Instance=2 Line=1
        EOFTk
